# Cloudflare Pages static-asset headers.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# Scope: the Lab SPA (served at /lab/). CSP delivery is required so
# the Turnstile explicit-render widget can load
# challenges.cloudflare.com scripts + iframe and reach its
# siteverify/challenge endpoints from the document response. CSP on
# JS/CSS asset responses is explicitly NOT part of the contract — the
# document CSP is what governs script execution.
#
# Two path patterns intentionally — `/lab` covers the no-trailing-
# slash form a few unfurlers/copy-pasted URLs use, `/lab/*` covers
# both `/lab/` (splat matches empty) and nested paths. Shipping both
# closes the "Turnstile blocked on the entry doc only" hole that the
# splat-only form left exposed when the route is served with a
# different canonicalization.
#
# Keep the popup-complete CSP in functions/auth/popup-complete.ts
# untouched: that CSP is scoped to the OAuth callback page and has no
# Turnstile dependency.

/lab
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-src https://challenges.cloudflare.com; img-src 'self' data: blob:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; connect-src 'self' https://challenges.cloudflare.com; font-src 'self' data:
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

/lab/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-src https://challenges.cloudflare.com; img-src 'self' data: blob:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; connect-src 'self' https://challenges.cloudflare.com; font-src 'self' data:
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
